CIVIL ACTION
NO. 20-3182
DECLARATION OF JARED ISAACMAN IN SUPPORT OF MOTION FOR
SUMMARY JUDGMENT
I, Jared Isaacman, declare as follows:
1. I am the Chief Executive Officer of Shift4 Payments, LLC (“Shift4”). I have held this
position since 2003. I have personal knowledge of the facts set forth herein and, if called as a
witness, could and would competently testify thereto.
2. I submit this declaration in support of Shift4’s Motion for Summary Judgment.
3. Shift4 is a leading provider of integrated payment processing and technology solutions.
Shift4 provides a single integration to an end-to-end payments offering, a powerful gateway, a robust
suite of technology solutions, and a wide range of software integrations.
4. Shift4 had actual knowledge that Card Connect, LLC (“CardConnect”) was and is an
authorized reseller of First Data and that, at least from in or around 2014 through 2017, CardConnect
was First Data’s largest reseller.
5. At no point since CardConnect was acquired by First Data in 2017 have I, or anyone
else at Shift4 to my knowledge, been confused as to whether Shift4 was soliciting a customer or partner
of CardConnect, First Data, or Fiserv. We knew who we were soliciting.
1
Case 2:20-cv-03182-MAK Document 68-13 Filed 06/27/22 Page 3 of 2 PageID #: 2218
6. As the CEO of Shift4, I regularly communicate with my employees on business-
related matters, including sales and marketing efforts.
7. I have never directed any Shift4 employees to falsely represent myself or themselves
as associated with First Data, Fiserv, or CardConnect.
8. Inever instructed or encouraged employees of Shift4 to engage in deceptive or
misleading behavior.
I declare under penalty of perjury under the laws of the United States of America that the
foregoing is true and correct.
